From 4868ee2a13acb2a6e44753968c33f6771159e7f4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ruzkypazzy <ruzkypazzy@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 16:17:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: use OKX Payment SDK (@okxweb3/x402-*) for x402 standard
 validation
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The DIY x402 wrapper passed the basic 402 challenge format but did not
perform EIP-3009 signature verification against the OKX facilitator, which
is what the OKX.AI ASP auto-reviewer checks. Switched to the official
@okxweb3/x402-express + @okxweb3/x402-evm + @okxweb3/x402-core stack:
- paymentMiddlewareFromConfig handles the 402 challenge with the exact
  PAYMENT-REQUIRED header format OKX expects
- ExactEvmScheme is the scheme that signs/validates EVM payments
- OKXFacilitatorClient hits OKX's /verify + /settle endpoints
- Facilitator creds are optional (OKX_FACILITATOR_API_KEY/SECRET/PASSPHRASE)
  — when missing, the SDK still emits a valid 402 for the auto-reviewer
  and rejects paid requests with a clear error
- x402RevisionGate and x402PackageGate both routes are now config-driven
  via the SDK's routes config (no more DIY if-else)
---
